@startuml document-family-architecture
' Editable UML master for the ADL document-family / layer architecture.
' Anchors: ADL Core §1.3 (The ADL Document Family); protocol overview (protocol/_next/index.md).
' Render to SVG: plantuml -tsvg document-family-architecture.puml
' The committed .svg is a hand-authored render; keep both committed (see diagrams/README.md).
'
' Patent note: FIG. 1 system-overview / apparatus. For the filing, re-render in B/W line art
' (no fills) and add the reference numerals below; keep numerals consistent across all figures.
'   100 ADL Core (declaration layer)      110 Agent Passport (declared, signed artifact)
'   120 declare<->enforce boundary        130 Trust Protocol (admission-time procedures)
'   140 Runtime Protocol (continuous)     150 runtime governor (within Runtime Protocol)
'   160 Enforcement Evidence record       170 open-layer extension slot

title ADL Document Family — Core Declares; the Protocols Enforce

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #334155

rectangle "DECLARE" as DECL #line.dashed {
  component "ADL Core\n(identity, capabilities,\nlimits, lifecycle)" as CORE
  artifact "Agent Passport\n(declared limits, signed)" as PASS
}

' Core sits directly above the passport; the passport is the hub the spokes fan out from.
CORE -down-> PASS : <<derive>>

rectangle "ENFORCE  (Protocol Layer)" as ENF #line.dashed {
  component "Trust Protocol\n(admission-time\nverification & authorization)" as TRUST
  component "Runtime Protocol\n(continuous governor:\nenforcement & evidence)" as RUNTIME
  component "Open-layer slot\n(discovery, reputation,\nsettlement)" as OPEN #line.dashed
}

artifact "Enforcement Evidence\n(hash-chained record)" as EVID

PASS --> TRUST : at admission
PASS --> RUNTIME : at runtime
PASS ..> OPEN : future
RUNTIME ..> EVID : <<produce>>

note bottom of OPEN
  Extension point: future protocols
  build on the same passport,
  with no change to the Core.
end note

@enduml
